@node ABOUT
@title "The game."

 To develop and create this game, we used the following software :

        HISOFT DEVPAC 2.15
             DELUXE PAINT IV
                IFF MASTER V1.0
                    PROTRACKER 3.15
                      AEGIS AUDIO MASTER
                         T.F.S. ARCHIVER / PETER BAKOTA -
                                                - MANX AZTEC C V3.6A

  This mindblasting game will put your wits at their peak performance,
 specially when 4 or 5 players take part. The objective is to blast all
 other players to win the round. When all rounds are playeed, the winner is
 annonounced.To use advantages of more than 3 players in game, you must
 have 4-player adaptor in parallel port. Maybe you don't have one ? Here is
 the connection table and simple picture to guide you. Numbers represent
 pins to be connected between connectors.

                                connectors
                  ___________________|__________________
                 |                   |                  |
                \|/                 \|/                \|/
             Joystick 3 |      Parallel port      | Joystick 4
            --------------------------------------------------
   pins ->        1      |     2      |     6      |    1
                  2      |     3      |     7      |    2
                  3      |     4      |     8      |    3
                  4      |     5      |     9      |    4
                  6      | 12,13*     | 10,11*     |    6
                  8      |    17      |    22      |    8

 NOTE : Numbers with * show pins to be short-connected.

  This is rough picture of connectors to show where each pin can be found,
 pins in connectors are numbered so finding the right pin should not be a
 problem.

                Joystick 3                         Joystick 4

             5_____________1                     5_____________1
              \ . . . . . /                       \ . . . . . /
               \ . . . . /                         \ . . . . /
              9 \_______/ 6                       9 \_______/ 6

                            Parallel connector

                      13_____________________________1
                        \ . . . . . . . . . . . . . /
                         \ . . . . . . . . . . . . /
                       25 \_______________________/ 14


 This adaptor will enable you to enjoy game with REAL LIVE PLAYERS IN
 IT, instead of playing with same dull computer-controlled images sliding
 over your screen.

    H A V E    T H E    R A A V E S T    F U N    A R O U N D  ! ! ! ! !

@endnode

@node HD_INSTALL
@title "HD-Installation."

  To install this game you just have to move TENABLASTER directory, using
 WB or, by using CLI, copy TENABLASTER.info file and TENABLASTER directory
 with its entire contents into desired directory.

@endnode

@node MAINSCREEN
@title "The Main setup-screen"

  After loading, you will encounter title screen, then the main game
 screen. Press fire to enter the "MAIN SETUP" screen. In middle of screen
 is list of options and at bottom of screen are ( left to right ) player
 image, disk image, bomb image, speaker image and items image.

 The options in list are :

 HARD BRICK
 Choose between 5 different types ( and one random mode ) of indestructable
 bricks, purely cosmetic.

 WINS NEEDED
 How many victory cups player needs to win the game.

 GHOSTS
 Number of ghosts to fill-in missing players while playing with less than 5
 players at the same time.

 SHOP
 Each player can, if he has any money, buy extras before each round.

 SHRINKING
 Since players can't battle to eternity ( unless you set time-limit to
 off ), battlefield will shrink ( shrinking = on ) or all players die when
 time runs out ( shrinking = off ).

 START MONEY
 Amount of money which will be available to spend in shop, BEFORE the first
 round.

 LEVEL
 The table types are : NORMAL - usual checkquered mapping, MAD - crazy
 labyrinths, NO WALLS - a clean field without hard bricks, RANDOM - a
 random choice of before mentioned, for each round.

 GAMBLING
  After each round one of the randomly chosen players will get an extra
 coin.

 TIME LIMIT
 This will suspend time limit and round will last until someone wins.

 TEAM MODE
 There are 3 team modes : NO - no team mode ( everyone for himself ),
 1 - players from same team will can walk over their own bombs,
 2 - nobody can walk across any bomb.

 FAST IGNITION
 This will enable / disable immediate explosion of controller bomb, when
 OFF, it enables player to set more than one bomb with controller.
 With the FASTIGNITION ON, TIMEBOMB WILL REPLACE CONTROLLER item. If
 FASTIGNITION is OFF, TIMEBOMB will enable immediate explosion for
 CONTROLLER bomb.

  Images on the bottom of main-setup screen : player image calls @{"player setup" link PLAYERSCREEN}
 screen, disk image invokes @{"configuration-save" link SAVECONFIG} requester, bomb image @{"starts" link STARTGAME}
 the game, speaker calls @{"soundbank setup" link SOUNDBANK} and items image calls @{"items setup." link ITEMSETUP}

@endnode

@node PLAYERSCREEN
@title "Player setup screen"

  On the PLAYER SETUP screen there five groups of images and two images at
 the left and right side of screen. Here is the schematics :

  _____________________________________
 |                  2                  |     1 - player ON / OFF
 |_____________________________________|     2 - player name
   __    __________   __________    __       3 - player image
  |1 |  |          | |          |  |5 |      4 - player type of control
  |__|  |          | |          |  |__|          ( joysticks 1 to 4 or
        |          | |          |                  keyboard )
        |    3     | |    4     |            5 - team color ( black team
        |          | |          |                or blue team )
        |__________| |__________|            6 - set soundbank ID
         _______     ___________                 ( 0 = default bank )
        |       |   |           |            7 - define keys for keyboard
        |   6   |   |     7     |                control
        |_______|   |___________|

 1 :
  Player may be switched on or off, depending on place and / or number of
 players involved in battle.

 2 :
  Player name field will give extra help when shopping or in winning
 screen ( it's nice to see your name in winner-screen, right ? ).

 3 :
  Player image gives you freedom to have image you like most. No other
 special tricks in it.

 4 :
  Control devices for player - one of 4 joysticks or keyboard. When the
 keyboard is selected, the icon number 6 lits.

 5 :
  Team colors are valid if team mode is 1 or 2. You can choose between blue
 or black team. Bombs set in team game are colored in team colors.

 6 :
  If you have Amiga with enough CHIP RAM, you can load upto 5 sample banks.
 After setting-up the sound banks, press fire at this icon to change bank
 ID.

 7 :
  Assuming you have selected keyboard control, you first have to bring
 pointer to icon number 6 ( the computer keyboard icon ) and press fire.
 Now, press keys as the flashing arrows ( for direction ) and - sign ( for
 fire ) appear as you define your favourite key-setup. Each arrow shows
 what function the key will be assigned to. If you have activated this by
 accident, you may cancel key control (re)definition by pressing the ESC
 key. Each player has its own key definition, to suit the need. NOTE : ESC
 ( cancellation ), F9 (main music on/off) and F10 ( game pausing ) keys are
 reserved.

  The bomb image at the left of screen will @{"start" link STARTGAME} the battle with 3-2-1
 countdown preparation and the text-document image will return you back to
 @{"main setup" link MAINSCREEN} screen.

@endnode

@node SAVECONFIG
@title "Configuration saving"

  This option on main-setup screen, the disk image, will invoke requester for
 configration saving which will ask you to confirm or cancel.

@endnode

@node STARTGAME
@title "Game start"

 When selected, battle begins after quick 3-2-1 countdown.

@endnode

@node SOUNDBANK
@title "Sound bank loading"

  We implemented ability for you to load your favourite samples into 5
 different soundbanks. These soundbanks are created with TenaBlaster
 soundbank creator. Be careful, these EAT chip-ram, so make sure you can
 load them ALL in memory !

 The samplebank entry scheme :

 _______________________________________
| A |               B               | C |
|___|_______________________________|___|

 A - bank ID
 B - bank file name
 C - delete bank file name

 Bank file name may contain path for finding file ( upto 16 chars
 maximum !). Soundbanks may be on different disk.

 EXAMPLES : BANK:sounds/MyBank.sbk     <- sounds (dir) in BANK: disk
            SYS:soundbanks/NewFX.sbk   <- soundbanks (dir) on BOOT disk

 The .sbk file name extension may be omitted, but it is recommended.
  On bottom are : @{"player setup" link PLAYERSCREEN}, loading sample banks, @{"start" link STARTGAME} game and @{"main" link MAINSCREEN}
 setup.

 To load bank from disk, activate disk icon.

@endnode

@node ITEMSETUP
@title "Item setup"

  Here are all items which you encounter in battle. Number next to each
 item shows number of occurances per battle round. Below is the name of
 current item and below that are : @{"player setup" link PLAYERSCREEN}, @{"start game" link STARTGAME} and @{"main" link MAINSCREEN} setup.
 To change, bring pointer to desired item and press and hold fire button.
 Now, move joystick left or right to decrease/increase the number. When on
 zero, item image darkens.

@endnode

@node ITEMS
@title "Items in game."

 The items are divided in two basic groups.

 Items, which you can buy in shop and in battle :

 EXTRA BOMB ( bomb with fuse )
  Well, game would't be much of a fun if you can't set a whole jumble of
 bombs ready to bang in your opponent's face, right ?

 POWER UP ( smiling flame )
  Your bombs won't be much of a effect with short ranged explosion. This
 one will increase explosion range.

 SUPERMAN ( superman sign )
  Why not - just roll over a normal brick over your neighbouring player
 splatting him like a pancake. Only one brick at the time can be pushed.
 If you can push the brick, that brick hides useful(?) item !

 CONTROLLER BOMB ( radio with antenna )
  When you get a controller, you will be able to send bomb away to any
 place you wish. As long as you hold down fire button, bomb will not explode
 and you can move it around, but when the fire button is released, bomb is
 armed ! If the FAST IGNITION is OFF, you may set more than one bomb this
 way ( if you get TIMEBOMB after controller, you have FAST IGNITION ON ! ).

 PROTECTION ( ying - yang sign )
  This will protect you during entire round, UNTIL you touch a skull or
 bomb explosion flame. Then the whitness will start to blink as a warning
 to remove yourself from hazardous enviroment and then it will disappear.

 GHOST ( ghost in wall )
  This one acts as protection aginst ANYTHING UNTIL you drop a bomb. You
 can actually pass trough walls ( not hard bricks ! ) so don't forget to
 set bombs in free space where you can manuver away from explosion ( else
 its bye - bye for you ... ).

 SPEED UP ( shoe )
  The need for speed can be satisfied with these. Beware, too much speed
 and you won't be able control your bomber ( what kind of alien are you if
 you CAN do it !? ).

 TIMEBOMB ( clock with fuse )
  This little devil allows you, while the fire button is pressed, to freely
 walk around bomb(s) you just set and detonate them by releasing fire
 button. They won't tick forever, even if you hold down fire button, they
 will eventually explode after a longer period of time so - don't forget to
 go away.


 Items which you can get ONLY in battle :

 RANDOM
  Random items ( INCLUDING SKULL or DISEASE ! ).

 CONTROL SWAPPER ( 4 red arrows )
  This one will reverse controls of all other players. Very effective when
 players have just dropped bombs or in hi-speed.

 ATOM BOMB ( white fungus-like cloud )
  When set, blows up one huge chunk of everything, including hard bricks.
 Can be used once only ( having this powerful bomb, you don't need TWO, do
 you ? ).

 NIGHT PLAY ( moon with stars )
  When used, it will dim the lights and battle field will get smoothly
 darker after each explosion.

 PERSON SWAPPER ( blue item with red arrows )
  Swapping items with other player(s). Watch out ! They will also able to
 trade their newly swapped items with others and those players will also be
 able to do the same ! It is spreading like a disease.

 SKULL
  Imminent death.

 STOP ( traffic stop sign )
  Paralyses all other players for a few seconds. Very nasty.

 MONEY ( golden $ coin )
  Money to buy extras in shop after a round.

 ICER MAN ( man in blue ice )
  Player can now temporarily freeze other players by touching them. Freezed
 players can't be killed while they are frozen.

 RANDOM TELEPORT ( a man in white fog )
  When used, the player will appear on randomly chosen spot on screen. Good
 if you wish to escape from destruction, bad because it can place you in
 very unpleasant position.

 FIRST AID ( red cross )
  Got sick from RANDOM item ? Disease can be either transferred to another
 player, or you may decide to cure yourself ?

 DETONATOR ( box with "d" on it )
  This item activates all bombs on battle field and detonation time depends
 on wether the FAST IGNIT is ON or OFF.

 PAC-MAN
  Player turns into pac-man, eating other players, bombs and items. Lasts
 short but kills everything except skull or explosion. If two pacmans meet,
 both loose.

 MONEY BAG ( bag with $ sign )
  This is very rare item. Player get 4 coins and all "equipment" is removed
 down to basics ( single bomb, 4 coins and basic speed ).

 THIEF ( "zorro" mask )
  Just "touch" player next to you and all of his money is transferred to
 your pockets. Single use only.

@endnode
